Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "ManipulateCaptionSection",ExpressionUUID->"86dada70-955a-4f17-ad47-131fc4106019"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The photoelectric effect is a quantum-mechanical phenomenon in which light \
impinging on the surface of a metal can cause electrons to be ejected. Only \
light with wavelengths shorter than some threshold value ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "0"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
  ExpressionUUID->"22e729d5-511f-44c8-9df4-151208f6ef56"],
 ", characteristic of each metal, can cause emission of photoelectrons, no \
matter how intense the radiation. Einstein explained this in 1905 by \
proposing that light is composed of discrete photons, each carrying energy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"E", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"h", " ", "\[Nu]"}], "=", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"h", " ", "c"}], "\[Lambda]"]}]}], TraditionalForm]], 
  "InlineMath",ExpressionUUID->"2e1ad478-3417-4875-93fb-dffbe00c1522"],
 ". Only when the photon energy exceeds the work function ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[CapitalPhi]", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",ExpressionUUID->
  "8be8746b-7be8-4f11-b8d5-b87135d84da7"],
 " of the metal, a measure of how strongly the outermost electrons are bound, \
can photoelectrons be emitted. The relevant equation is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
     FormBox[
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"h", " ", "c"}], "\[Lambda]"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
     ExpressionUUID->"8d8d8d52-6783-49fc-adc3-d5c1fd61fb8a"]], "InlineMath",
     ExpressionUUID->"d17b2a28-c2b4-45e6-9e59-9ba8e0370739"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalPhi]", "+", 
     SubscriptBox["KE", "max"]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
  ExpressionUUID->"90c6465c-3c47-4951-b45d-86108ac544c1"],
 ", where the last term represents the maximum kinetic energy of the ejected \
electrons. Once the threshold wavelength is attained, the current of \
electrons increases linearly with the radiation intensity. This can be \
monitored by an ammeter in the circuit shown. The light source covers the \
entire visible range 400\[Dash]700 nm. In the ultraviolet region, the light \
ray appears as black."
}], "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.35696210375764*^9, {3.414278994430193*^9, 3.414279096771659*^9}, {
   3.4143402111256275`*^9, 3.4143402268131275`*^9}, {3.41434142042511*^9, 
   3.414341444611526*^9}, {3.4145215987973166`*^9, 3.414521617640946*^9}, {
   3.686419164548448*^9, 
   3.686419191348555*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"50f2f95a-4683-4324-80a4-\
58930dbbff42"],

Cell["\<\
Einstein was awarded the 1922 Nobel Prize in Physics for his theory of the \
photoelectric effect, rather than for his discoveries of the special and \
general theories of relativity. \
\>", "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.35696210375764*^9, {3.414278994430193*^9, 3.414279096771659*^9}, {
   3.4143402111256275`*^9, 3.4143402295318775`*^9}},
 CellID->60519243,ExpressionUUID->"40e32f56-3082-48dd-b328-38f4c110d480"]
}, Open  ]],

